This paper deals with the development of distributed, asynchronous probabilistic reasoning systems, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The systems being discussed involve multiple autonomous entities that interact with each other, which suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems (cs.SY). The use of dynamic models to account for changes in the system over time suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and possibly multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
